    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="459" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <head>No. 459.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Manning</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-05-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 2,
                            1887</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No 96.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 116, of the 14th
                        ultimo, relative to the recent troubles at Nogales.</p>
                <p>The Department is pleased to notice the friendly tone of Mr. Mariscal’s
                        private letter to you, and it is hoped that his official note, soon to be
                        written, and the prompt and thorough punishment of Gutierrez will terminate
                        the Nogales incident.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
